main event: Four witnesses observed two light-colored, circular objects in the sky over Tallahassee, Florida, on August 22, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were larger than an average aircraft and were observed at relatively low altitude.,Witnesses reported two separate sightings, with durations of 2-3 minutes and 10-15 minutes.,The objects moved slowly without sudden or erratic movements.,No physical evidence was found from the sightings.,All witnesses provided hand-drawn sketches of the objects, although no photographs were included.
